						               													<description>It is a competitive game between 2 and 6 players. On their turn, each player must perform one of the 8 challenges, in a time of one minute. If they succeed, they win the token for that challenge. Whoever gets the 8 different tokens wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 8 challenges are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Memory: remember a sequence of 8 cards with objects.&amp;#10;     Language: make words with 2, 3 and 4 letters.&amp;#10;     Translation: translate a Roman number to an Arabic number.&amp;#10;     Visual: alternately say the written word and its ink color.&amp;#10;     Identification: recognize which card is missing.&amp;#10;     Repetition: read a tongue twister and repeat it without mistakes.&amp;#10;     Logic: find the fourth card that is deduced by Logic.&amp;#10;     Deduction: a question is read and its relationship is deduced.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a game conceived, created and developed by neuroscience specialists dedicated to the study of the human brain. The objective is to provide a playful tool that helps improve mental functions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
